modules.description: Provides functions to generate arbitrary commands, initialize and transition between states, and manage a system under test. Operates with custom types `cmd`, `state`, and `sut` to model command execution and state changes. Used to implement property-based testing workflows with randomized command sequences and state tracking.

Provides functions for parsing and evaluating simple arithmetic expressions, including addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division. Works with strings representing expressions and returns evaluated numeric results. Used to implement basic calculator logic in embedded systems.

Provides functions to generate arbitrary commands based on a state, transition between states using commands, and manage a system under test. Works with custom types for commands, states, and system instances. Used to execute and validate command sequences in property-based testing scenarios.
